Getaway | The vehicle newly weds "getaway" in varies, depending on the couple and their personality. A few years ago, two close friends got hitched and rode off in this 1961 Oldsmobile. It was parked out front at their reception, illuminated only by bulb lights and fire from torches and candles. The car belonged to the groom's father. It resided in a barn in Montana for over two decades while the family lived in Point Clear, Alabama (Montana is where the family lived originally, and kept property in the state when they moved down south). Eventually, the car made its way to Alabama after the groom's brother and father drove it across country. This car held so many childhood memories for the groom, but even more with his new bride. It is the sams car he drove the day he proposed, so it's only fitting it was the car the couple drove away in after celebrating their new life with family and friends. @thisisalabama @natgeoyourshot [11/7/15]

Few people know we have a blended family. In total there are six children I'm responsible for sending to college 💰 Like many in similar situations, the last ten years has been rocky. With limited time, influence and communication it's been a true struggle to find balance, faith and even positivity! As a stepmom, it's easy to feel devalued or disrespected, esp when dealing with a past divorce. Despite the difficulties, I am so thankful to have a big family - to extend my influence and be another example of strength, hard work, resilience and honor. I was so grateful when my husband genuinely said thank you as we neared the end of our trip to Alabama, where my stepchildren live. It wasn't on any special day, triggered by any special moment - it was a genuine realization that I could've left, but I didn't. I chose to love hard, live hard and fight hard on this non-traditional route with him. ❤️❤️❤️#blendedfamily #spanishfort #alabama #marriage #mariakang
